description:
Here’s the schedule for CodeJam 14 ✨

We have an exciting weekend ahead of us!! Looking forward to welcoming you all on Friday 🙈🫶
Introducing our incredibly beautiful, hardworking, and talented executive team! We’re all so excited to welcome you to CodeJam this weekend 🥰🤩

The FINAL Web Dev workshop is on November 21th from 6-8pm in McConnell 304! 🤖🤖🤖

Build on what you learnt in the first few workshops (or just rip the last workshop no sweat) - this is the perfect opportunity to prepare for CodeJam this weekend!

Sign up at our link in bio!

Meet more of the incredible sponsors of CodeJam 14! Thank you to all our sponsors for making this event possible.

If you want a chance to network with sponsor representatives, join us at our Tech Fair this Friday (open to all students, not just CodeJam participants)🕺🏽🕺🏽
We’re so excited to announce the sponsors behind CodeJam 14!! Thank you so much to all of our sponsors for your support. Stay tuned for part 2 🤗

The second Web Dev workshop is on November 14th from 6-8pm in McConnell 304! 🤖🤖🤖⭐️⭐️🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🏃‍♂️🏃‍♂️💻💻👾🎮🎮🎮🎮🎮⚡️⚡️⚡️

Build on what you learnt in the first workshop (or just rip the second workshop no sweat) with intro to react, css, connecting to an API, and some HTML and JavaScript.

Sign up at our link in bio!

The first Web Dev workshop is now on November 12th from 6-8pm! 🕺💻🕺💻

Come get your first introduction to frontend, backend, how websites work, databases, APIs, popular tech stacks, and setting up a project. 

Sign up at our link in bio!

Calling all tech pros! Mentor and judge applications for CodeJam 14 are OPEN 💻🌟 If you love hackathons and want to give back to the tech community (and enjoy some free food), this is your chance! We welcome upper year students and grads with development experience.

Applications are in the link in our bio. Sign up now to be a part of CodeJam’s biggest and best event yet 🤗

Quaking in fear about CodeJam approaching and you still only know to write a for loop? Or perhaps looking to finally get around to making your personal website? WELL the Factory x CodeJam has all your needs covered🤝

Join us in our four part workshop series where we go from the basics all the way to building your own site! The four workshops coming up are:

1. Intro to Web Dev
2. More frontend essentials (HTML, CSS, JS)
3. Put together a personal site 
4. Connect everything to the backend

Workshops 3 and 4 are tailored to your specific needs and will help you prepare to slay CodeJam or make that personal website to wow recruiters 🤩💻🕺

Stay tuned for the locations and signups for each workshop coming soon.
